  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Prospective cohort study of consecutive diabetic patients undergoing percutaneous coronary
      intervention (PCI) in whom development of critical limb ischemia was prospectively assessed
      by a dedicated diabetic foot clinic. Cardiac mortality at 4-year follow-up was the primary
      endpoint of the study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
